Website - Bhuvan Tourism 
Website URL - https://bhuvan-app1.nrsc.gov.in/tourism/tourism.php
Website Content Details - 
Bhuvan Tourism is a WebGIS platform developed by the National Geospatial Data Center (NGDC) of the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). It is a web-based application that provides access to a wide range of geospatial data and information related to tourism in India. The platform includes data on tourist destinations, attractions, facilities, and infrastructure. It also provides tools for planning and managing tourism activities.

Bhuvan Tourism is a valuable resource for anyone interested in tourism in India. It can be used to:

Research tourist destinations and attractions
Plan and manage tourism activities
Promote tourism in India
The platform is available in English and Hindi. It can be accessed from any computer with an internet connection.

Here are some of the features of Bhuvan Tourism:

Access to a wide range of geospatial data and information: Bhuvan Tourism provides access to a wide range of geospatial data and information related to tourism in India. This includes data on tourist destinations, attractions, facilities, and infrastructure.
Tools for planning and managing tourism activities: Bhuvan Tourism provides tools for planning and managing tourism activities. These tools can be used to:
Research tourist destinations and attractions
Plan itineraries
Book accommodations and transportation
Get travel information
Promotion of tourism in India: Bhuvan Tourism can be used to promote tourism in India. The platform can be used to:
Create and share tourism content
Market tourism destinations
Attract tourists to India
Bhuvan Tourism is a valuable resource for anyone interested in tourism in India. It is a comprehensive and user-friendly platform that provides access to a wide range of geospatial data and information.


